.TH "LIGHTNING-CHANNEL-CLOSE-ALL-PEERS" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-channel-close-all-peers \- mutually close all normal channels with a peer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning channel-close-all-peers
.I peer_id
.SH DESCRIPTION
Closes every
.B CHANNELD_NORMAL
channel with the specified
.I peer_id
by calling
.B lightning-cli close
on each one.
Returns an error object if the daemon is unreachable.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"peer_id":..., "closed":[{channel_id, ok},...]}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-channel-close (1),
.BR lightning-node-close-all (1)
